                            <comment id="16362909" author="githubbot" created="Tue, 13 Feb 2018 19:22:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user jeking3 commented on the issue:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1465&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1465&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    I found a check-in to hxcpp around October 2017 which enabled C++11 by default; I had to disable it by setting this environment variable: `export HXCPP_CPP11=0` in the ubsan build script.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16364299" author="githubbot" created="Wed, 14 Feb 2018 15:46:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user jeking3 commented on the issue:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1465&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1465&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    I am tired of waiting for failed builds, I am going to do this work in my fork&apos;s CI environment where I can control the builds.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16364300" author="githubbot" created="Wed, 14 Feb 2018 15:46:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user jeking3 closed the pull request at:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1465&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1465&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16368513" author="jensg" created="Sun, 18 Feb 2018 10:37:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Last time I checked only the PHP part was affected. So disabling PHP output may be enough.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
